From 30d79469d04756760b6617f3ecddf059851ef220 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 14:27:49 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 01/42] [displayxr inline-3d #625 B2a] browser-process weave
 client + vendored OpenXR
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Step B / B2a — de-risk Seam C (linking + process boundary). Adds a flag-gated
(--enable-inline-3d) DisplayXR weave client to content_shell's BROWSER process
(unsandboxed; the GPU sandbox blocks the per-frame RPC to displayxr-service, see
docs/roadmap/webxr-step-b-design.md). It creates a forced-IPC OpenXR instance,
confirms XR_EXT_weave + win32_window_binding + KHR_D3D11, and resolves the weave
entry points.

- third_party/displayxr: vendored OpenXR loader (1.1.43) + DisplayXR extension
  headers + BUILD.gn (openxr_loader group; stages openxr_loader.dll next to the
  exe). Zero vendor/weave code.
- content/shell/browser/displayxr_weave_client.{h,cc}: OpenXR-free facade header
  + Windows-only impl, isolated source_set with relaxed (non-chromium) warnings.
- Hooked at ShellBrowserMainParts::PreMainMessageLoopRun; off by default.

Validated on Leia: log shows D3D11=1 win32_window_binding=1 display_info=1
weave=1 and bindWindow/submit/snap PFNs resolved — B2a PASSED. Per-frame weave +
browser<->GPU Mojo bridge land in B2b/B2c.
